description:
OM Materials (S) Pte Ltd (“OMS”) , based in Singapore, is a wholly-owned subsidiary of OM Holdings Limited, that handles the logistics, procurement, marketing, and distribution activities of the Group. 
 With a long history of marketing ores and ferroalloys, OMS possesses an extensive trade network and an edge in connecting raw materials with buyers and users. Originally established in the 90s focusing on the raw materials trade in China, its scope and range of action have since evolved to a global scale, albeit retaining an Asian focus. 
 Collectively, OMS leverages the economies of scale of the Group’s operations to streamline raw material procurement and product sales. This is made possible by comprehensive product knowledge and a strong operational expertise in international trade execution. 


 About this role 
 This program is meant for fresh graduates or those with a few years of working experience, looking to start their career in the world of physical commodities. The program is an accelerated induction experience, with an emphasis on learning by doing. Trainees will work on physical operations across global markets and be given real responsibilities to help develop practical skills and competencies. Candidates should be highly motivated and interested in building a long-term career in the company. 


 Trades Trainee 
 Job responsibilities: 

  Opportunity to be exposed to: Sales, Purchasing, Logistics, Operations; 
  Logistics and shipping documentation; 
  Additional exposure to other functional areas such as mining, smelting, material processing; 
  Frontline sale/purchase execution and risk management; 
  Long term business development, sales planning, and strategy; 
  Manage relationships with buyers, sellers, and service providers; 
  Data compilation, research and analysis; Ad-hoc traveling as and when required. 



 Requirements: 

  Degree in relevant discipline, demonstrated academic achievements, entry level candidates welcome; 
  Analytical and strong logical thinker, results oriented; 
  Self-driven team player, a good listener and good communicator; 
  Systematic and organized, able to thrive under pressure and situational ambiguity; 
  Excellent written and spoken communication in English and Chinese to liaise with counterparts.

JOB DESCRIPTIONS: 

  Assist in preparing project tender submission including bills of quantities, check tender drawing, material specifications, prepare and submit the P&S plan, shop drawing, & other required documents; 
  Assisst in preparing and submit monthly progress claims, VO, finalization of accounts; 
  Assist in taking measurement of quantities and cost estimation; 
  Assist in liaising with Managers, Team Members, Customers, Sub-Contractors and Suppliers; 
  Purchasing and inventory management; 
  Administrative tasks and ensure the office runs smoothly and work towards a good place to work for the team; Perform other duties as assigned. 



 REQUIREMENTS: 

  Minimum Diploma and above in Quantity Surveyor or equivalent. 
  Fresh graduates and intern is welcome. 
  Able to work independently with minimum guidance and under pressure to meet tight schedules. 
  Good team player with strong interpersonal and communication skills. 
  Proficiency in AutoCAD Immediate starter or short notice is an advantage 




 SHOULD YOU KEEN TO THE POSITION , PLEASE APPLY ONLINE ONLY . 
 OR EMAIL TO MAIN@WSG.COM.SG . 
 ONLY SHORTLISTED APPLICANTS WILL BE NOTIFIED .

This is a graduate program with job rotation exposure and learning in various departments. 


 In your new role you will: 


  Manage the Distribution Centre outbound shipments fulfilling transit time requirement and freight cost optimization; 
  Work closely with logistic service provider , including warehouse, Customs and Quality operations to fulfill the defined service KPIs; 
  Engage service provider account management team, taking lead in driving continuous improvement in processes and systems; 
  Drive problem solving in daily shipping operation by performing problem analysis and implement corrective action ; 
  Prepare performance reports , data analytics and recommendation to management for mid / long term improvement.




 You are best equipped for this task if you have: 


  Bachelor's Degree in Business/Operations Management/Logistics & Supply Chain ; 
  Entry level candidates will be welcome to apply 
  Relevant working experience especially in Shipping/Forwarding/Logistics ; 
  Strong analytical and problem solving skills; 
  Experience in logistics service provider management; 
  Process and system improvement/ Project Management experience; 
  SAP/Assist4 hands-on experience/knowledge will be an advantage;






